==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zoilism
<hw>Zo"i*lism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Resemblance to
Zoilus in style or manner; carping criticism; detraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bring candid eyes the perusal of men's works, and let not
<qex>Zoilism</qex> or detraction blast well-intended labors.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zoisite</ent>⟦br⟧
